<!-- WHY THIS AREA -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Inner north character suburb with value relative to Windsor and strong city connectivity.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Lutwyche sits about five kilometres north of the CBD, sharing postcode 4030 with Windsor and bordered by Red Hill and Kelvin Grove to the south, and Kedron to the north. The Lutwyche Road corridor that runs through the suburb connects residents to the CBD by frequent bus, while the shopping centre precinct and the surrounding commercial strip provide practical day-to-day amenity. The suburb's reputation in the wider market has historically been dominated by its main road, but the residential streets behind that corridor are a different proposition entirely.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
<div style="background:#fff; border-left:4px solid #c4912a; padding:2rem 2rem 1.75rem; margin:2rem 0;">
